                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#9va">Fol. 9va</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 9va: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘወኃበቶ፡ ለደብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ሰውኔ፡ ስመ፡ አቡሃ፡ ወልደ፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡ ወስመ፡ እማ፡ ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወስመ፡ አኃቲሃ፡ …</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that the Ms. was donated to the monastery of Däbrä Maryam Säwne. It mentions the name of the donor’s family members but does not reveal the name of the female donor. 
The note is written in the same hand that inserted the name ʿAmätä Maryam into supplication formulas throughout the Ms.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#9vb">Fol. 9vb</locus>: Testament of wäy[zä]ro Tʿǝbe Kahsay (?)  <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in Amharic and sealed with signatures and a fingerprint.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#81ra">Fol. 81ra</locus>: Excerpt from the hymn ʾǝsäggǝd lä-mäläkotǝkä... “I worship Thy Godhead…”.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Crudely written.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#81rb">Fol. 81rb</locus>-va: Sälam läki Maryam dǝngǝl zä-mäʿaza ʾafuki kol … “Salutation to you Virgin Mary, your mouth is of apple fragrance ...” (cp. ChRep no. 91).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Crudely written.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#84r">Fol. 84r</locus>: Unclear note. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in Amharic and Tǝgrǝñña (?) and sealed with signatures and two fingerprints.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fol. 83rv (included in quire B) contains an excerpt from the Psalter (Pss. 132-133), in the main hand.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names of the donors are frequently left unfilled: fols. 7va, 11va, 15vb, 19rb etc.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 5va, 8ra, 8vb, 22vb, 33vb, 35ra, 40vb, 44ra, 60vb.&#xD;
- Thin black lines for line filling on fol. 12va.&#xD;
- Scribbles on fol. 2v.&#xD;
- Crude drawings on fols. 1v-2r.</item>
                     </list>
